{{Infobox award | name = 1st Primetime Emmy Awards | image = | caption = | date = January 25, 1949 | location = [[Hollywood Athletic Club]], [[Los Angeles]], California | presenter = [[Academy of Television Arts and Sciences]] | host = [[Walter O'Keefe]] | network = [[KCBS-TV|KTSL]] | producer = | main = {{nowrap|[[Primetime Emmy Award]]s}} | next = [[2nd Primetime Emmy Awards|2nd]] }}
The '''1st Emmy Awards''', retroactively known as the '''1st Primetime Emmy Awards''' after the debut of the counterpart [[Daytime Emmy Award]]s, were presented at the [[Hollywood Athletic Club]] in [[Los Angeles]] on Tuesday, January 25, 1949. Only shows produced in Los Angeles County, California and aired in the Los Angeles [[media market]] were eligible to win. The awards were hosted by [[Walter O'Keefe]] who substituted for [[Rudy Vallée]] when he had to leave town at the last minute. A special award category was introduced and awarded to [[Louis McManus]] for designing the actual Emmy Award statuette.
