{{distinguish|text=[[SAIC Motor]], which used to use the Shanghai name before changing to SAIC.}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Shanghai International Automobile Industry Exhibition | native_name = 上海国际汽车工业展览会 | native_name_lang = zh | logo = | image = The 2009 Shanghai International Auto Show.jpg | caption = Auto Shanghai 2009 | status = Active | genre = [[Auto show]] | begins = | ends = | frequency = Biennial | venue = National Center for Exhibition and Convention (Shanghai) | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | country = China | years_active = 1985-present | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | area = | budget = | activity = | patron = | organised = | filing = <!-- Filing status --> | people = | member = | website = {{ URL | 1=http://auto-shanghai.expopromoter.com/ }} }}
'''Auto Shanghai''' ({{zh|上海国际汽车展}}), officially known as the '''Shanghai International Automobile Industry Exhibition''' ({{zh|上海国际汽车工业展览会}}), is a biennial [[Auto show|international automobile show]] that alternates with the [[Beijing Auto Show]] (Auto China) as China's yearly international automotive exhibition.<ref name="www.prnewswire.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/cgi-bin/stories.pl?ACCT=104&STORY=/www/story/11-21-2006/0004478432&EDATE=|title='Technology and Nature in Harmony' - The 12th International Automobile & Manufacturing Technology Exhibition Reaches its Peak Next Spring - SHANGHAI, China, Nov. 21 /Xinhua-PRNewswire}}</ref> First held in 1985, Auto Shanghai is the nation's oldest auto exhibition, and is considered as an important major [[international auto show]].<ref name="cardesignnews.com">{{cite web|url=http://archive.cardesignnews.com/autoshows/2005/shanghai/highlights/index.php |title=Shanghai Motor Show 2005 - Highlights |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080122030941/http://archive.cardesignnews.com/autoshows/2005/shanghai/highlights/index.php |archivedate=22 January 2008 |df=dmy }}</ref>
Due to the greatly expanding presence of foreign brands in the Chinese markets, Auto Shanghai has become one of the premier international auto shows alongside Detroit, Frankfurt, Paris and Tokyo, and was also the first Chinese auto show to join the [[Union des Foires Internationales|UFI]]. Since 2015, the show is hosted at the [[National Center for Exhibition and Convention]], located next to the [[Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport]].__NOTOC__
==2017== The 2017 show ran from 19 April to 28 April. * 19–20 April — Press & VIPs preview * 21–23 April — Trade visitors preview * 24–28 April — Open to the public
